  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Lab 7 — Fine-Tuning & Distillation\n",
    "**Train a smaller, cheaper model to behave like your best agent**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why this matters\n",
    "\n",
    "Every agent in this course uses `gpt-4o` or `gpt-4o-mini` for every call. That works for prototypes. In production, costs compound fast:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Scenario | gpt-4o cost | Fine-tuned gpt-4o-mini cost | Saving |\n",
    "|----------|-------------|------------------------------|--------|\n",
    "| 10k tool-call decisions/day | ~$25/day | ~$1.50/day | **94%** |\n",
    "| 1M classification calls/month | ~$2,500 | ~$90 | **96%** |\n",
    "| Structured output extraction | ~$0.005/call | ~$0.0003/call | **94%** |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Fine-tuning** teaches a smaller model to match the quality of a larger model on *your specific task*.  \n",
    "**Distillation** is how you generate the training data: use the big model (teacher) to label examples, then train the small model (student) to match.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "gpt-4o (teacher)\n",
    "    ↓ generates high-quality responses for your use case\n",
    "Training dataset (JSONL)\n",
    "    ↓ fine-tuning job\n",
    "gpt-4o-mini (student) — now matches teacher quality at 1/15th the cost\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## What you'll build\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Distillation pipeline** — use `gpt-4o` to generate labelled training data for a specific agent task\n",
    "2. **JSONL dataset builder** — format data correctly for OpenAI fine-tuning\n",
    "3. **Fine-tuning job** — submit the job via the OpenAI API and monitor it\n",
    "4. **Quality gate** — run Lab 2's eval suite on the fine-tuned model before promoting it\n",
    "5. **Cost vs quality tradeoff** — measure the actual score gap between teacher and student\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key packages:** `openai`, `pydantic`, `json`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "part1-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 1 — Choose Your Task\n",
    "\n",
    "Fine-tuning works best for tasks that are:\n",
    "- **Repetitive** — the same pattern executed thousands of times\n",
    "- **Well-defined** — clear right/wrong answers, not open-ended creativity\n",
    "- **Latency-sensitive** — smaller models respond faster\n",
    "\n",
    "**Good candidates:**\n",
    "- Intent classification (`book_flight` / `check_balance` / `cancel_order`)\n",
    "- Structured data extraction (parse an invoice → JSON)\n",
    "- Tool-call routing (which tool should the agent call for this input?)\n",
    "- Output formatting (always respond in a specific JSON schema)\n",
    "- Domain-specific Q&A (your product's docs, your company's policies)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Poor candidates:**\n",
    "- Open-ended reasoning or creative writing\n",
    "- Tasks requiring up-to-date knowledge (model's knowledge is frozen at training)\n",
    "- Tasks with fewer than ~50 examples (too little signal)\n",
    "\n",
    "**For this lab:** We'll fine-tune for **intent classification** — a core decision point in nearly every agent system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import time\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "from openai import OpenAI\n",
    "from pydantic import BaseModel\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv(override=True)\n",
    "client = OpenAI()\n",
    "\n",
    "TEACHER_MODEL = \"gpt-4o\"        # generates training data — high quality, higher cost\n",
    "STUDENT_MODEL = \"gpt-4o-mini\"   # will be fine-tuned — cheaper, faster\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Teacher: {TEACHER_MODEL}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Student (to be fine-tuned): {STUDENT_MODEL}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "part2-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 2 — Distillation: Generate Training Data with the Teacher\n",
    "\n",
    "The teacher model (`gpt-4o`) generates high-quality labelled examples.  \n",
    "We collect these as a JSONL file — the format OpenAI fine-tuning expects.\n",
    "\n",
    "**JSONL format:** one JSON object per line, each with `messages` (system + user + assistant).\n",
    "\n",
    "```json\n",
    "{\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"...\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"...\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"...\"}]}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Dataset size guidance\n",
    "\n",
    "| Use case | Minimum examples | Sweet spot |\n",
    "|----------|-----------------|------------|\n",
    "| Classification (3–5 classes) | 50 | 150–300 |\n",
    "| Structured extraction | 100 | 300–500 |\n",
    "| Style/tone matching | 200 | 500–1000 |\n",
    "| Domain Q&A | 300 | 1000+ |\n",
    "\n",
    "This lab generates 30 examples (fast demo). For production, scale to 150+."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "define-task",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define the task: classify customer support messages into intents\n",
    "\n",
    "INTENTS = [\"book_flight\", \"cancel_booking\", \"check_status\", \"request_refund\", \"general_inquiry\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are an intent classifier for an airline customer support system.\n",
    "Classify the user's message into exactly one of these intents:\n",
    "- book_flight: user wants to book a new flight\n",
    "- cancel_booking: user wants to cancel an existing booking\n",
    "- check_status: user wants flight status or tracking info\n",
    "- request_refund: user wants a refund\n",
    "- general_inquiry: anything else\n",
    "\n",
    "Reply with only the intent label, nothing else.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Seed messages covering all intents with varied phrasing\n",
    "SEED_MESSAGES = [\n",
    "    # book_flight\n",
    "    (\"I need to fly from New York to London next Tuesday.\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"Can you help me find a flight to Tokyo in March?\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"I'd like to book two seats to Paris for my anniversary.\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"What's available from LAX to Miami this weekend?\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"Book me on the earliest flight to Sydney tomorrow.\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"I want to travel to Berlin, what are my options?\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    # cancel_booking\n",
    "    (\"Please cancel my reservation for flight AA123.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"I need to cancel my trip, something came up.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"How do I cancel a booking I made last week?\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"I want to cancel both legs of my round trip.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"Cancel everything on booking reference XYZ789.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    # check_status\n",
    "    (\"Is my flight BA456 on time?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"Where is flight UA789 right now?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"My flight was supposed to leave an hour ago, any updates?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"Has the gate changed for AA100?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"What's the arrival time for DL200 from Chicago?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    # request_refund\n",
    "    (\"I want my money back for the cancelled flight.\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"How long does a refund take?\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"I was charged twice for one seat, please refund.\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"My flight was delayed 8 hours, I'm owed compensation.\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"Can I get a full refund if I cancel today?\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    # general_inquiry\n",
    "    (\"What's your baggage allowance policy?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "    (\"Do you serve meals on short-haul flights?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "    (\"Can I bring my pet on board?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "    (\"What ID do I need for a domestic flight?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "    (\"Is there wifi on your transatlantic routes?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Seed messages: {len(SEED_MESSAGES)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Intent distribution: {dict((i, sum(1 for _, x in SEED_MESSAGES if x==i)) for i in INTENTS)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "generate-data",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# COST: ~$0.05 (25 teacher calls with gpt-4o, simple classification task)\n",
    "# For production: generate 150+ examples. Scale by adding more seed messages\n",
    "# or asking the teacher to generate variations.\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_teacher_label(message: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Ask the teacher model to classify a message.\"\"\"\n",
    "    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=TEACHER_MODEL,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": message},\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0,  # deterministic — we want the teacher's best answer\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "def to_training_example(message: str, label: str) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Convert a (message, label) pair to OpenAI fine-tuning JSONL format.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"messages\": [\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": message},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": label},\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate training data using the teacher\n",
    "print(\"Generating training data with teacher model...\")\n",
    "training_examples = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (message, expected_label) in enumerate(SEED_MESSAGES):\n",
    "    teacher_label = get_teacher_label(message)\n",
    "    match = \"✅\" if teacher_label == expected_label else \"⚠️\"\n",
    "    print(f\"  {match} [{i+1:2d}] {teacher_label:20s} | {message[:50]}\")\n",
    "    # Use the teacher's label (not our seed label) — the teacher may know better\n",
    "    training_examples.append(to_training_example(message, teacher_label))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{len(training_examples)} training examples generated.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "save-dataset",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split into train (80%) and validation (20%)\n",
    "import random\n",
    "random.seed(42)\n",
    "random.shuffle(training_examples)\n",
    "\n",
    "split = int(len(training_examples) * 0.8)\n",
    "train_set = training_examples[:split]\n",
    "val_set   = training_examples[split:]\n",
    "\n",
    "def write_jsonl(examples: list, path: str):\n",
    "    with open(path, \"w\") as f:\n",
    "        for ex in examples:\n",
    "            f.write(json.dumps(ex) + \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "write_jsonl(train_set, \"ft_train.jsonl\")\n",
    "write_jsonl(val_set,   \"ft_val.jsonl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train: {len(train_set)} examples → ft_train.jsonl\")\n",
    "print(f"  Val: {len(val_set)} examples → ft_val.jsonl\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Preview of first training example:\")\n",
    "print(json.dumps(train_set[0], indent=2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "part3-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 3 — Submit the Fine-Tuning Job\n",
    "\n",
    "OpenAI fine-tuning is a two-step process:\n",
    "1. **Upload** the JSONL files to OpenAI's file storage\n",
    "2. **Create** the fine-tuning job pointing at those files\n",
    "\n",
    "The job runs asynchronously — usually 10–30 minutes for small datasets.  \n",
    "You get a fine-tuned model ID like `ft:gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18:your-org::abc123`.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Cost\n",
    "OpenAI charges per token for fine-tuning training (not inference).  \n",
    "For 25 examples (~500 tokens each) × 3 epochs ≈ 37,500 tokens ≈ **~$0.45**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "upload-files",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Upload training and validation files\n",
    "print(\"Uploading training file...\")\n",
    "with open(\"ft_train.jsonl\", \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    train_file = client.files.create(file=f, purpose=\"fine-tune\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Train file ID: {train_file.id}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Uploading validation file...\")\n",
    "with open(\"ft_val.jsonl\", \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    val_file = client.files.create(file=f, purpose=\"fine-tune\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Val file ID:   {val_file.id}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "create-job",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 2: Create the fine-tuning job\n",
    "job = client.fine_tuning.jobs.create(\n",
    "    training_file=train_file.id,\n",
    "    validation_file=val_file.id,\n",
    "    model=STUDENT_MODEL,\n",
    "    hyperparameters={\n",
    "        \"n_epochs\": 3,          # 3 passes over training data — good default for small datasets\n",
    "        \"batch_size\": \"auto\",   # OpenAI picks optimal batch size\n",
    "        \"learning_rate_multiplier\": \"auto\",\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    suffix=\"intent-classifier\",  # appended to the model ID for easy identification\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Fine-tuning job created!\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Job ID:  {job.id}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Status:  {job.status}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Model:   {job.model}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"The job runs asynchronously — typically 10–30 min for this dataset size.\")\n",
    "print(\"Run the next cell to poll for completion, or check the OpenAI dashboard:\")\n",
    "print(\"  https://platform.openai.com/finetune\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "poll-job",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Poll for job completion (runs until done or failed)\n",
    "# If you close the notebook, just re-run this cell with the job ID from above.\n",
    "JOB_ID = job.id  # or paste a job ID here: JOB_ID = \"ftjob-abc123\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Polling job {JOB_ID}...\")\n",
    "while True:\n",
    "    status = client.fine_tuning.jobs.retrieve(JOB_ID)\n",
    "    print(f\"  [{time.strftime('%H:%M:%S')}] Status: {status.status}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if status.status == \"succeeded\":\n",
    "        fine_tuned_model = status.fine_tuned_model\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n✅ Fine-tuning complete!\")\n",
    "        print(f\"   Fine-tuned model ID: {fine_tuned_model}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"   Add to .env: FINE_TUNED_MODEL={fine_tuned_model}\")\n",
    "        break\n",
    "    elif status.status == \"failed\":\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n❌ Job failed: {status.error}\")\n",
    "        break\n",
    "    \n",
    "    time.sleep(60)  # poll every minute"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "part4-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 4 — Evaluate: Teacher vs Student\n",
    "\n",
    "Before using the fine-tuned model in production, measure the quality gap between teacher and student.  \n",
    "The goal is **not** to match the teacher perfectly — it's to be *good enough* at a fraction of the cost.\n",
    "\n",
    "A fine-tuned gpt-4o-mini typically achieves **95–99% of gpt-4o quality** on narrow classification tasks."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "eval-setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load fine-tuned model ID (set after job completes)\n",
    "fine_tuned_model = os.getenv(\"FINE_TUNED_MODEL\", \"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not fine_tuned_model:\n",
    "    print(\"Fine-tuned model not set. Run the polling cell above first,\")\n",
    "    print(\"then set: fine_tuned_model = 'ft:gpt-4o-mini-...'\")\n",
    "    # For demo purposes, fall back to base gpt-4o-mini\n",
    "    fine_tuned_model = STUDENT_MODEL\n",
    "    print(f\"Using base {fine_tuned_model} for demo comparison.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Held-out test cases (not used in training)\n",
    "TEST_CASES = [\n",
    "    (\"I need to get to Rome by Friday, what flights do you have?\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"Please cancel booking ref ABC999.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"My flight leaves in 2 hours, is it on time?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"The airline cancelled my flight, I want a full refund.\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"Are there vegetarian meal options?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "    (\"Book me a business class seat to Dubai next month.\", \"book_flight\"),\n",
    "    (\"I changed my mind, cancel my reservation.\", \"cancel_booking\"),\n",
    "    (\"Has flight LH400 landed yet?\", \"check_status\"),\n",
    "    (\"How much compensation do I get for a 5-hour delay?\", \"request_refund\"),\n",
    "    (\"Can I upgrade to first class at the airport?\", \"general_inquiry\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Evaluating on {len(TEST_CASES)} held-out test cases\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run-eval",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# COST: ~$0.02 (20 calls: 10 teacher + 10 student, simple classification)\n",
    "\n",
    "def classify(message: str, model: str) -> str:\n",
    "    r = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=model,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": message},\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return r.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"{'Message':<45} {'Expected':<20} {'Teacher':<20} {'Student':<20}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 105)\n",
    "\n",
    "teacher_correct = 0\n",
    "student_correct = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for message, expected in TEST_CASES:\n",
    "    teacher_pred = classify(message, TEACHER_MODEL)\n",
    "    student_pred = classify(message, fine_tuned_model)\n",
    "\n",
    "    t_ok = \"✅\" if teacher_pred == expected else \"❌\"\n",
    "    s_ok = \"✅\" if student_pred == expected else \"❌\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    teacher_correct += teacher_pred == expected\n",
    "    student_correct += student_pred == expected\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"{message[:44]:<45} {expected:<20} {t_ok} {teacher_pred:<18} {s_ok} {student_pred}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 105)\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy — Teacher ({TEACHER_MODEL}): {teacher_correct}/{len(TEST_CASES)} = {teacher_correct/len(TEST_CASES):.0%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy — Student ({fine_tuned_model[:30]}): {student_correct}/{len(TEST_CASES)} = {student_correct/len(TEST_CASES):.0%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "part5-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 5 — Cost vs Quality Tradeoff\n",
    "\n",
    "The decision to use a fine-tuned model is a **cost-quality tradeoff**, not a binary choice.  \n",
    "Here's how to think through it for your own use case."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cost-analysis",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cost comparison: teacher vs fine-tuned student at scale\n",
    "# Prices as of May 2026 (USD per 1M tokens)\n",
    "\n",
    "PRICING = {\n",
    "    \"gpt-4o\":                {\"input\": 2.50,  \"output\": 10.00},\n",
    "    \"gpt-4o-mini\":           {\"input\": 0.15,  \"output\": 0.60},\n",
    "    \"gpt-4o-mini (ft)\":      {\"input\": 0.30,  \"output\": 1.20},  # fine-tuned costs 2x base\n",
    "    \"gpt-4.1-nano\":          {\"input\": 0.10,  \"output\": 0.40},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Typical classification call: ~200 input tokens, ~5 output tokens\n",
    "INPUT_TOKENS  = 200\n",
    "OUTPUT_TOKENS = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "def cost_per_call(model_key):\n",
    "    p = PRICING[model_key]\n",
    "    return (INPUT_TOKENS / 1_000_000 * p[\"input\"] +\n",
    "            OUTPUT_TOKENS / 1_000_000 * p[\"output\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "DAILY_CALLS = 10_000\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Cost comparison for {DAILY_CALLS:,} classification calls/day\\n\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Model':<25} {'Per call':>10} {'Daily':>12} {'Monthly':>12} {'vs gpt-4o':>12}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 73)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline = cost_per_call(\"gpt-4o\") * DAILY_CALLS\n",
    "for model_key in PRICING:\n",
    "    cpc = cost_per_call(model_key)\n",
    "    daily = cpc * DAILY_CALLS\n",
    "    monthly = daily * 30\n",
    "    saving = (1 - daily / baseline) * 100\n",
    "    print(f\"{model_key:<25} ${cpc*1000:>8.4f}‰  ${daily:>10.2f}  ${monthly:>10.2f}  {saving:>10.0f}% cheaper\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print()\n",
